./frontend-components/src/FormattedDateI.description:
A number of API endpoint return dates as ISO8601 strings and some don't with/without timezone designators. Example:

```json
{
  "departureDateTime": "2018-04-26T13:50:00.000+02:00",
  "arrivalDateTime": "2018-04-26T17:50:00.000+01:00"

  "departureDateTime": "Sat, 26 Apr 2018 13:50:00 +0200",
  "arrivalDateTime": "Sat, 26 Apr 2018 17:50:00 +0100"
}
```

In case of ISO8601 strings, the purpose of these strings is dual:
- to unambiguously build a `Date` object using
  e.g. [`Date.parse()`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Date/parse)
- to explicitly set the timezone in which the date should be displayed. The timezone is defined by the
  [timezone designator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_zone_designators) at the end of the string.

The `FormattedDateInItsTimeZone` component takes as value any date string (with/without a timezone designator) and
formats the date represented as it is in UTC. This can be thought of as "stripping" the timezone if the timezone is
mentioned. The component passes to the renders an ISO8601 string constructed in UTC.


The component has a similar API to that of [FormattedDate](https://github.com/yahoo/react-intl/wiki/Components#formatteddate),
hence, additional properties can be passed to it to instruct the formatting.

./frontend-components/src/ReactNativeWeb.description:
React Native Webview component with injected Omio cookies
@see See [RN Webview API reference](https://github.com/react-native-webview/react-native-webview/blob/master/docs/Reference.md)

`WebView` settings
1. Cookie headers passed in the source will be set as a cookie inside the webview only if they are listed as essential cookies here:
     https://github.com/goeuro/app/blob/41ce7c273128ac218b0cf2d9ba9c778daf3755cd/services/app/lib/propagate-essential-cookies.js#L43
2. if incognito false:
   - all cookies will be persisted between `WebView` views,
   - headers passed in source will be injected only on the first view
3. PLEASE do not inject authorization cookie to webview using injectedJavaScript...  properties
